8/5/2026:
Product / feature: Lecture Intelligence upload pipeline on Next.js App Router (TypeScript, Tailwind, shadcn/ui).

What shipped:

- Dashboard (/dashboard) with drag-and-drop (and file picker), optional subject field, upload list with status.
- Supabase: @supabase/ssr — browser client (src/lib/supabase/client.ts), server client (src/lib/supabase/server.ts), middleware.ts for session refresh + protecting /dashboard.
- Flow: prepareUpload server action → insert uploads row → createSignedUploadUrl → browser XHR PUT for upload progress → startProcessing sets processing_parse and enqueues FastAPI via after() + PYTHON_SERVICE_URL / INTERNAL_API_KEY (src/lib/processing/enqueue-job.ts).
- UX: optimistic rows (preparing / uploading / starting), Realtime on uploads for refreshes, loading.tsx on dashboard.
- Removed monolithic src/lib/supabase.ts in favor of client + server.
- Docs under docs/ (architecture, DB schema, AI/parsing/product PRD, SM-2, etc.) and @supabase/ssr in package.json.
- Git: Committed on master as 32591db (“Add lecture upload pipeline with Supabase storage and processing enqueue”) and pushed to origin/master (lectureintelligence). src/types/uploads.ts was included as the truncated “+1” file so imports typecheck.

Env expectations: NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_*, optional PYTHON_SERVICE_URL + INTERNAL_API_KEY; Supabase uploads bucket + uploads table + RLS per docs/database-schema.md.

